<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer6452318436156954935">Antonio Tabucchi was an Italian writer and academic who taught Portuguese language and literature at the University of Siena, Italy.<br/><br/>Deeply in love with Portugal, he was an expert, critic and translator of the works of the writer Fernando Pessoa from whom he drew the conceptions of saudade, of fiction and of the heteronyms. Tabucchi was first introduced to Pessoa&apos;s works in the 1960s when attending</span>
  <span id="freeText6452318436156954935" style="display:none">Antonio Tabucchi was an Italian writer and academic who taught Portuguese language and literature at the University of Siena, Italy.<br /><br />Deeply in love with Portugal, he was an expert, critic and translator of the works of the writer Fernando Pessoa from whom he drew the conceptions of saudade, of fiction and of the heteronyms. Tabucchi was first introduced to Pessoa's works in the 1960s when attending the Sorbonne. He was so charmed that, back in Italy, he attended a course of Portuguese language for a better comprehension of the poet.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6452318436156954935" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
